cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes the web as a graph and studies the distributions of degree and sizes of strongly/weakly connected components. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper deals with web crawling and analyzing web data. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is a possibility as the paper may involve software tools and techniques for web crawling and graph analysis. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possibility as the paper deals with graph analysis and shortest path lengths. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but the paper may touch upon issues related to the impact of the web and its graph structure on society.
